We have to agree that the Russell Wilson-Denver Broncos' relationship is not working!

#nflverse #RStats #ggplot2 https://t.co/2GHhzIB6CA

Posted a couple of these last week. I've changed the code so it includes designed runs for QB's as well. Here's Jalen Hurts without rushes and with the rushes, so you can see the difference. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/Wzxjs7AtFd

Here's the comparison you all want to see. Patrick Mahomes vs Josh Allen. Mahomes's 2022 looks a lot like his 2020 season, complete with an unfortunate dip toward the end of the season. Allen's 2022 is all dip, but might be rising now. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/5BnML8YAcy

The other vaunted AFC West QB's. In case you're wondering, dropping off the chart at the bottom is B A D bad. Russ managed to break both the top AND the bottom, which is just wild. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/t1viUbe8fp

Here's Dak and Lamar. Dak has been really consistent since his high in 2019. He's just really solidly good. Lamar's 2019 was INSANE!!! Unfortunately, a pretty strong downward trend since then, with a couple lifts. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/xITyXsemwt

Can't help but think that the #Jets would be shoo-in the playoffs if they didn't lose Breece Hall. The dude is a specimen. 

#nflverse https://t.co/xaT58OO2SF
